# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Expert_Smart — Docker build context exclusions (REPO-ROOT FILE)
#
#  Why this file lives here, not in deploy/:
#  Docker reads .dockerignore only at the build-context root. Compose sets
#  context: .. (the repo root) for the Flask service, so this is the path
#  Docker actually checks. The file in deploy/ is preserved as historical
#  documentation only.
#
#  Source of truth for the heavy-path exclusions: April 26, 2026 audit
#  (build context was 1.16 GB; ~1.07 GB of that is non-runtime data).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ─── Standard housekeeping (mirrored from deploy/.dockerignore) ─────────
.git
.gitignore
.vscode
.idea
__pycache__
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.pytest_cache
.coverage
.env
.env.local
*.log
*.bak
*.swp
.DS_Store
node_modules/
build/
dist/
tests/

# ─── Generated artifacts (regenerated inside the container) ─────────────
outputs/
core_engine/outputs/
*.docx
*.pdf

# ─── RAG / vector store data (mounted as Docker volumes in production) ──
core_engine/data/embeddings/
core_engine/data/qdrant_local/
expert_smart_system/vector_db/
expert_smart_system/vector_db_new/

# ─── Heavy non-runtime paths (the audit's primary culprits) ─────────────
# LLM adapter weights — runtime uses Ollama, not local adapters
expert_smart_system/models/
expert_smart_system/extracted_docs/
expert_smart_system/expert_model_final.zip

# Historical operator-side fixtures — Flask routes accept payloads via HTTP,
# they do not read inputs/raw_docs/ at runtime
core_engine/inputs/

# Embedded venv — must never go into a container
core_engine/banking_expert/venv/

# ─── Legacy spreadsheet templates and samples (active ones are .xlsx/.xlsm) ──
*.xls
EXAMPLE.xls

# ─── Excel template carve-out ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Excluding *.xlsx and *.xlsm wholesale would also drop the active
# valuation/REIT/EIA report templates that bridge_api.py opens. Exclude
# everything except the exact template files referenced by the code.
*.xlsx
*.xlsm
!core_engine/templates/template.xlsx
!core_engine/templates/template.xlsm
!templates/template.xlsx
!templates/template.xlsm
